</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="container">
  <h1>Search</h1>
  <p class="sub">Start typing to filter results instantly</p>
  <div class="search-box">
    <i class="fas fa-search"></i>
    <input id="search" type="text" placeholder="Search articles, docs, components..." autocomplete="off">
    <div class="spinner" id="spinner"></div>
  </div>
  <div class="meta"><span id="count">12 results</span><span id="time"></span></div>
  <div class="results" id="results"></div>
</div>
<script>
const DATA = [
  {title:'Getting Started with React',desc:'Learn the fundamentals of React including components, props, and state management.'},
  {title:'CSS Grid Layout Guide',desc:'A comprehensive guide to CSS Grid including named areas, auto-fill, and subgrid.'},
  {title:'TypeScript Generics Explained',desc:'Understanding generic types, constraints, and utility types in TypeScript.'},
  {title:'Authentication with JWT',desc:'Implement secure authentication using JSON Web Tokens and refresh token rotation.'},
  {title:'Responsive Design Patterns',desc:'Mobile-first techniques including fluid typography, container queries, and responsive images.'},
  {title:'API Error Handling',desc:'Build robust error handling with custom error classes, retry logic, and user-friendly messages.'},
  {title:'Performance Optimization',desc:'Lazy loading, code splitting, memoization, and rendering optimization techniques.'},
  {title:'Accessibility Fundamentals',desc:'ARIA labels, keyboard navigation, focus management, and screen reader compatibility.'},
  {title:'State Management Patterns',desc:'Comparing useState, useReducer, Context API, Zustand, and server state with React Query.'},
  {title:'Database Design Basics',desc:'Normalization, indexing strategies, query optimization, and schema design principles.'},
  {title:'WebSocket Real-time Apps',desc:'Building real-time features with WebSockets including reconnection and heartbeat patterns.'},
  {title:'Testing React Components',desc:'Unit testing with Jest, component testing with Testing Library, and E2E with Playwright.'}
];

const searchInput = document.getElementById('search');
const resultsEl = document.getElementById('results');
const countEl = document.getElementById('count');
const timeEl = document.getElementById('time');
const spinner = document.getElementById('spinner');
let activeIndex = -1;
let debounceTimer;

function highlight(text, query) {
  if (!query) return text;
  const regex = new RegExp('(' + query.replace(/[.*+?^${}()|[\]\\]/g,'\\$&') + ')', 'gi');
  return text.replace(regex, '<mark>$1</mark>');
}

function render(query) {
  const start = performance.now();
  const q = query.toLowerCase().trim();
  const filtered = q ? DATA.filter(d => d.title.toLowerCase().includes(q) || d.desc.toLowerCase().includes(q)) : DATA;
  const elapsed = (performance.now() - start).toFixed(1);

  countEl.textContent = filtered.length + ' result' + (filtered.length !== 1 ? 's' : '');
  timeEl.textContent = elapsed + 'ms';
  activeIndex = -1;

  if (filtered.length === 0) {
    resultsEl.innerHTML = '<div class="empty">No results found. Try a different search term.</div>';
    return;
  }

  resultsEl.innerHTML = filtered.map((d, i) =>
    '<div class="result" style="animation-delay:' + (i * 0.04) + 's" onclick="alert(\'Opening: ' + d.title.replace(/'/g,"") + '\')">' +
    '<div class="title">' + highlight(d.title, query) + '</div>' +
    '<div class="desc">' + highlight(d.desc, query) + '</div></div>'
  ).join('');
  spinner.classList.remove('show');
}

searchInput.addEventListener('input', (e) => {
  spinner.classList.add('show');
  clearTimeout(debounceTimer);
  debounceTimer = setTimeout(() => render(e.target.value), 200);
});

searchInput.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
  const items = resultsEl.querySelectorAll('.result');
  if (e.key === 'ArrowDown') { e.preventDefault(); activeIndex = Math.min(activeIndex + 1, items.length - 1); }
  if (e.key === 'ArrowUp') { e.preventDefault(); activeIndex = Math.max(activeIndex - 1, -1); }
  if (e.key === 'Enter' && activeIndex >= 0) { items[activeIndex]?.click(); }
  items.forEach((el, i) => el.classList.toggle('active', i === activeIndex));
  items[activeIndex]?.scrollIntoView({ block: 'nearest' });
});

render('');
</script>
</body>
</html>
```

Features: Sora font, 200ms debounced search with loading spinner, text highlighting on matches, keyboard navigation (arrow keys + Enter), result count and query time, staggered fade-in animation, empty state, responsive. Pure vanilla JS, no dependencies.

They do the same thing — memoize a value between renders — but for different types of values.

**useMemo** memoizes a **computed value:**
```jsx
const filtered = useMemo(() => {
  return items.filter(i => i.category === selected)
}, [items, selected])
// Returns the RESULT of the function
```

**useCallback** memoizes a **function itself:**
```jsx
const handleClick = useCallback((id) => {
  setSelected(id)
}, []) 
// Returns the FUNCTION, not its result
```

`useCallback(fn, deps)` is actually just `useMemo(() => fn, deps)`. They're the same mechanism.

**When to use each:**

- **useMemo**: expensive calculations that you don't want to re-run every render. Filtering a 10,000 item list. Sorting. Complex transformations. NOT for cheap operations — the memoization overhead isn't worth it for simple lookups.

- **useCallback**: when you pass a callback to a child component wrapped in `React.memo()`, or when a function appears in a `useEffect` dependency array. Without useCallback, the function is recreated every render, which means the memo'd child re-renders anyway, or the effect re-runs.

**When NOT to use them:**

Most of the time. If you're not seeing a performance problem, don't add them. They add complexity, use memory for the cached value, and the comparison itself has a cost. Measure first, optimize second.

```jsx
// DON'T do this — premature optimization
const name = useMemo(() => user.name, [user.name]) // just use user.name
const onClick = useCallback(() => setOpen(true), []) // unless child is memo'd, pointless
```

